Your Honor,

I am Robert Chapman, and I stand before this court today to plead guilty for the offense of speeding that I have committed. I take full responsibility for my actions and deeply regret the danger I put others in.

In all honesty, my curiosity got the best of me, and I couldn't resist pushing the limits of my brand-new car to see how fast it could go. I now realize the grave risk I took and the potential consequences that could have occurred.

I sincerely apologize for my negligence in not promptly responding to the Notice of Intended Prosecution (NIP). I must admit that I tend to overlook my mail, and sadly, I did not see the notice. However, I want to assure you that if I had been aware of it, I would have immediately taken the necessary steps to address the situation.

It is true that I do have previous penalty points on my license from three prior speeding incidents. However, I would like to highlight that, apart from these driving offenses, I have maintained a clean record without any further involvement in criminal activities.

Your Honor, I willingly accept my guilt for this offense and fully acknowledge the consequences that come with it. I humbly ask for your understanding as you consider the circumstances surrounding my case. I assure you that I have learned a valuable lesson from this experience, and I am committed to conducting myself responsibly and obeying all traffic laws in the future.

