Furthermore, I failed to respond to the Notice of Intended Prosecution (NIP) that was sent to me. I apologize for my neglect in regularly checking my mail, which prevented me from promptly addressing the situation. I genuinely regret this oversight and acknowledge that it was entirely my fault.

I believe it is important for me to acknowledge that this incident has served as a turning point in my life. It has allowed me to reflect on the gravity of my actions and understand the impact they can have on others. As a result, I have taken proactive steps to educate myself on responsible driving practices through defensive driving courses.

By entering a guilty plea today, I hope to demonstrate my acceptance of full responsibility and genuine remorse for my behavior. I understand the importance of taking accountability for my actions, and I see this plea as a crucial step towards making amends.

I humbly request Your Honor's consideration and understanding of the unique circumstances surrounding my case. I am committed to learning from this experience and making the necessary changes to become a responsible driver. I assure you that I will diligently address any penalties or consequences imposed by the court.

I would like to express my gratitude for your attention to this matter and for granting me the opportunity to take full accountability for my actions. I sincerely appreciate Your Honor's understanding and consideration.

Respectfully,
Robert Chapman
